content.detailedDescription: I found these objects recently when looking back on photos from a trip to the czech republic last year. i do not remember whether or not i was aware of the objects while the photos were taken, but i do seem to remember thinking they were quite odd. they could have been birds, or perhaps foreign objects on the lens, but all pictures before and after do not have any such objects, and the passage of time in between the photos would suggest that these objects were not birds or known aircraft. the town were these photos were taken has some history of ufos and the paranormal, including a crop circle that appeared in 2014.
content.summary: Black cigar or saucer. possibly a bird.

the middle of my forehead started tingling, 
imprint of a perfect triangle is on my hand now.
content.summary: I was laying in bed when i heard a loud buzzing outside my window

content.detailedDescription:
A business associate and i were in our main conference room conducting our regular weekly meeting. she had her back to the window and i was facing it when from the corner of my eye i saw something white move horizontally across. i was sure it was a bird so initially i ignored it but when it happened a 2nd time and stayed floating in front of the window, i stood up and asked my colleague to come to the window.
what we saw was a shiny, mercury colored object that looked to be in the shape of stingray. without the long tall but had a sort of domed shape in the middle. the odd part was that it moved around like a stingray would in the water, was held together but appeared to be in a liquid form.
it moved slowly around the the window from west to east, the whole time staying at eye level with us. at times it would drop down but then slowly rise up to our eye level. the whole time we were about 5-10 feet away from this object. these were the windows facing south.
then it decided to move over to our east side windows, hovering as it did, without a sound, just like a mercury liquid sting ray.
we both lost track of the time but then all of a sudden, from a dead stop, the object moved from where we were to the mount saint-hilare bird sanctuary in about 1 or 2 seconds, a distance of 50 km. there was a cloud over the mount and we could see a shiny spec, which was about the size we could see it now, up straight into the clouds.
the odd part was is that my colleague and i never said a word to each other nor did we ever discuss what we had experienced at the office.
after the event, i went to my office to pick up my things and went straight home, not speaking to anyone. to this day i find it hard to believe what i say but there is no mistake in what i saw.
content.summary: A liquid mercury type object advanced upon us as we stared out the window of our office building. moving west to east it went around us and then suddenly sped off 50 km away in a matter of seconds and disappeared into a cloud.

content.detailedDescription: Bright light shined through the window i leaned up to wake my dad up but he wouldnt wakeup i looked at the window and to my supprise there was 4 grey aliens standing there then i blacked out. i was 4 years old and did not know about aliens at the time i have remembered this my entire life its burned into my mind. i have tried to find a hypnotist in michigan who would help me remember more but have faild in finding one can anybody help me?
content.summary: Grey alien abduction

content.detailedDescription: i had just applied for a job at the local university and decided to stop at the performing arts plaza to get a nice view of the bay and eat a snack. it was raining lightly and overcast, so looking from the plaza, the first thing that caught my eyes were the plumes on the horizon from a petroleum plant that operates a few miles northwest of my location. inside the plumes was a rectangle-shaped dark patch that was moving away from the mass of smoke. i watched it with curiosity for a few minutes because of the odd, dark shape, but discounted the object as a dense cloud of smoke that simply hadn't dispersed in the wind. after the object had cleared the smoke, it was an obvious rectangle shape, but i instead assumed it was a flight from vancouver or overseas, coming in for landing at the local international airport. i began eating and watching, noting the slowness with which the object moved across the sky. after 15 minutes, the object was lined up with the airport from my perspective and also began diminishing and returning from its black rectangular shape into a black square, similar to looking at a dead pixel on a computer screen. the rectangle would also slowly drift halfway to it's starting position and back again. my belief that this was an aircraft began wavering, so i turned the zoom to maximum on my phone camera and filmed a few (shoddy) shots of the object for posterity. after filming, i saw a jet take off from bellingham international airport and watched it transit the rectangle. the jet was almost as big as the object, but clearly closer to me, giving me the notion that this object was much larger than the jet. i continued waiting, watching two helicopters pass over the bay and one more jet taking off from the airport. i had expected to see the rectangle bank and land at the airport, considering that i may have misidentified an aircraft waiting for landing clearance, but instead, to my surprise i saw the object drift slightly westaward one last time, ascend a few more degrees away from the horizon and slowly vanish into the black 'pixel' shape, as though it's distance from me had significantly increased. the last i saw of it was a slow fade into obscurity among the clouds. during the majority of the sighting, i was convinced the object was a large distant aircraft, but in conclusion, all of its behaviors and drifting patterns defy explanation by myself.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Gigantic black rectangular prism hovering around international airport before takeoff

content.summary: Frame structure multi triangles gold transparent glow structure faded into glow white light

content.detailedDescription:
Craft was shaped like a top, about three feet wide at the top. top tapered to bottom which was about one foot wide. fire engine red with no sign of doors or windows. overall size was five feet high by three feet across at widest top of craft. at the bottom was a light, too bright to look at, rotating throughout the sighting. 


firstly i sighted a flashing light which was too brilliant to look at - about seven miles down a divided four-lane straight and level highway - no trees along highway except in the distance where craft first sighted. it was travelling toward me just over a very low power line along the highway. the power line it was over was, at the most, 50 feet from my car and built below the roadway in the ditch. when the craft passed me it would not have been more than twenty-five feet above me as it travelled only about twenty feet or less above the power line. it was travelling at a speed which was slightly faster than my car (60 mph) and the cars in oncoming lane. it came toward my vehicle at a steady rate over the power line, without wavering; although there was a wind of about 100+ mph that afternoon around 5 pm. (extreme strong winds are common in this area.) as the craft came closer, i could see the light at the bottom was rotating but too bright to look at. 

i watched the approximate ten minutes it took to travel along the road toward my vehicle. it passed me and continued down the highway over the power line until i lost sight in my rearview mirror. it made absolutely no sound.

i watched for sighting reports in our local paper and on tv that evening and next day as the highway was very busy with after work traffic. i never saw a report of any kind which left me stunned. i, also, did not report the sighting to anyone as i had my newborn daughter in the car next to me and felt someone else would report as many, many people had to have seen what i saw - close up in the early summer afternoon!

i watched the craft intently making note of the size very carefully and searched the red craft for any sign of doors/windows. the exterior appeared to be solid with no cracks for a door or window. a smaller man would have been able to sit inside but a tall man would not have been able to stand erect.
content.summary: First sighted incredible light 7 miles ahead of highway.  craft travelling 20 feet over power line in roadway ditch. it passed me about 25 feet above road height and continued on above power line. did not waver in strong wind.

content.altitude: 500 Feet or Less, Over 500 Feet (no cloudcover)
content.detailedDescription:
We noticed the sparkling shining copper crown like circle hovering in sky while playing in backyard with brother and friends. we followed it to the street discussing colorful gem like lights. that night i had horribly traumatic abduction "dream" waking next morning.
the dream felt much more than a dream. strange unrecognizable beings came after all of my family yet my mom, dad and two older brothers were separated from me while they ran out the house seeking refuge via glass doorway of nextdoor neighbor's basement. followed them the best i could locating where they fled. but moment i reached backyard nextdoor basement doors to rejoin my family, i unable to open basement door plus my family sat at the door staring out towards me hypnotized immovable wouldn't unlock basement door to let me in. i pleaded loudly please let me in. they refused. i struggled to avoid the beings but they grabbed me. returning home, they landed on front yard in early morning bringing me. my parents ran out of house to meet us begging they return me home like they had agreed the day before. my parents (in this dream) said the beings promised they wouldn't do anything to hurt me. beings discussed various things with my parents assuring them nothing bad would happen. my parents said please don't come to bother us anymore. i woke up next morning around 10 am, sleeping very late, which was very unusual, running to my brother and parents relating what happened. all of us slept late yet nobody else thought anything happened.
content.flightPath: Hovering then path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Sparkling shining copper crown circle in sky while playing in backyard with brother and friends. we followed it to the street discussing colorful gem like lights. that night i had horribly traumatic abduction "dream" waking next morning.

content.detailedDescription:
Ufo sighting
i was about to enter a bar when i noticed a green and red light hovering in the sky.  there was something off about these lights.  they seemed familiar, but not, at the same time.  i watched the lights and they did not move nor did they blink.  there was the sound of a "helicopter" but there were several things that didn't make sense, if it was a helicopter... first the lights did not blink (this is against faa regulations).  second, if it was a helicopter looking for something, it was at night, no lights were emitted from it, and it was way too high in the air to spot anything on the ground with out the use of spot lights.  so i believe it was a ufo emitting the sound of a helicopter.  so i proceeded to take multiple videos of the object.  as i am doing so, i realize there are literally hundreds of lights that appear and disappear around this main green and red light.  i could not see any of the hundreds of blinking lights with my naked eye.  it was only by filming this green and red light that the camera picks them up.  that's what truly blew me away.  so i'm left with video that clearly shows something odd.  my friend that was with me doesn't believe in ufo's and says it was just a helicopter... but the video shows something much different.  again, helicopter lights blink... these did not.  ...And i literally don't know what to think about the hundreds of flashing lights seen on the video, as my eyes could not pick them up; just the camera.
content.summary: Hovering solid light with several moving blinking lights surrounding it

content.detailedDescription: Witnessed ufo moving slowly toward us, very large object, seeming to respond to our high-beam flashlight. it continued to spotlight back to us until directly over us, the light enormous. it was a bright golden/ amber color; it appeared in these huge bursts like a star that would explode continuously above us. my husband would flicker the flashlight like morse code. the ufo seemed curious and made no sound as it made several passus over us, seeming to lose interest. the ufo stopped it's light and suddenly vanished. there was some cloud cover that prevented us from seeing the craft in it's entirety. we filmed it but video picture would not capture anything. we stargaze often, especially moving north of the military base have we now seen craft we cannot explain. we understand the sounds and sights of military, commercial jets, small communicating, taxi lighting and drones. what made this special was the lack of noise, the size of the light and the apparent attempts at communicating. we were in awe, no fear.
content.summary: Ufo makes contact

content.detailedDescription:
July 4, 2016, 10:37 pm mdt
location: worland, wyoming, 44n 108w
i am located about 6 miles out of town and was at my neighbor’s house enjoying the fireworks around the valley.  at 10:37 pm, a bright light, white in color, caught my attention overhead.  the sky was clear with possibly a very thin overcast and stars clearly shining through and no moon.  my first thought was it might be fireworks but there was no “trail” and explosion and it was way too high.  

the object was about as bright as venus at its brightest and several times larger.  it moved slowly from due south to north covering approximately 20 degrees of arc.  next i thought it might a satellite or the iss but unless they changed its orbit, the iss doesn’t fly a polar orbit.  this was definitely a polar orbital flight path.  what makes me think there was a thin overcast is the light “plumed”.  the object itself got very bright and a “halo” effect surrounded it opening to about 1 degree or a little more than the diameter of a full moon would appear on the horizon.  the halo looked like it might be the exhaust of a rocket going away from me and after perhaps 10 – 15 seconds the object dimmed to a star point and disappeared.  

as for its location in the sky, it traversed roughly 15 – 20 degrees of arc 3 – 5 degrees west of celestial zenith and 5 south of zenith to about 15 degrees north of zenith.

i tried finding information about any nasa launches but nothing came up for this timeframe.  i googled “space launches july 4 2016” but nothing showed.  might this have been a vehicle launch into a higher orbit or something else along that line?   what i do know is it was definitely not a meteor, comet, fireball or the infamous “swamp gas” of michigan.  there was no sound except from people around the valley firing off fireworks and by that hour only a few people were doing so anyway.  please let me know what you figure out.  i am curious as to what we saw.  i might have to invest in a “smart phone” because taking video with my “dumb phone” takes too many steps and i didn’t want to miss observing this thing; whatever it was.

on a personal note, i am retired air force and an air force navigator/electronic warfare officer as well as a private pilot.  i am also an amateur astronomer.  

thank you
capt. gene leone (ret) usaf
content.summary: Intense bright light extreme altitude moving due south to north

content.detailedDescription: So, i was at a friends hanging out with a few people. it was late and we went to the living room to watch a movie. i remember my friend putting the movie in the vcr, (yes, i said vcr) and i remember sitting on the couch and seeing a light from the big window behind me. i turned around to look out the window to see who it was thinking it was a car pulling in. i didnt know this persons house well so it didnt strike me until after that the position on the driveway theres no way the lights could have been facing our direction. so i looked out the window and the light got really bright. thats the last thing i remember before i remember sitting on a diffrent part of the couch (it was a sectional) and asking another friend aside of me what happend. he just said its okay your fine. almost like he was trying to calm me down for being upset over nothing. like you would talk to a comfort a child when their lollypop drops in the dirt and its the end of the world for the child but your cool and collected. i couldnt figure out why noone was feeling the anxiaty and confusion i was. i remember looking at the t.V. and seeing the credits down the screen. and just being very overwhelmed. noone talked about these lights or what i felt just happend at all. like nothing happend. again adding to my confussion. i instantly felt isolated, and honestly a little crazy. this happend about 11 years ago. ive told one person. its not something i talk about with people but in my head i feel like ive kinda become obsessed trying to logically explain what happend that night. ever since my attention has been drawn to the skies. i find myself always looking up, i just cant explain it.
content.summary: Bright light, bright flash, missing time

content.detailedDescription:
I have seen the most bizarre thing this afternoon over tywyn in gwynnedd north wales uk. we regulary see raf and us jets trianing in the mountains and valleys here during the working week, and they frequently fly something called the 'mach loop' which is a well known circuit they follow.
 
however today at approx 12:30pm we heard this really weird humming noise in the sky almost like electro static energy or a sub station would make, and we look out over the see and saw this weird looking triangle shaped aircraft or craft (see attached images). it was moving really slowly about 5-10mph about 200m off the coast like just to the south of tywyn off the beach moving in a northern direction. i was walkign my dogs in the sand dunes at the time. now i am ex raf and i have a very good knowledg of all military aircraft but i have never seen anything like this. it was no drone or uav and was the size of a raf typhoon fighter jet. as it moved up the coast line it dropped two bright red coloured glowing spheres down into the sea and they disappeared. i quikcly got this shot on my iphone of the thing as it moved off and just after i took this image, it stopped in mid air, moved upwards and then just disappeared. i called the coastguard but they said nothing unusual had been reported.
 
i think this was a ufo because it was certainly nothing we are the americans have in terms of military technology or aircraft. it was intelligently controlled almost in an over the top way.
 
my wife and i saw this as well as two other dog walkers one of which called the local police to report it.
 
can you report on this as i definately thing this is a ufo or something not from this world.
 
many thanks
content.flightPath: Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Triangle ufo over coastline in broad daylight

content.detailedDescription: I was walking home, between 12:20 am and 12:45 am. i noticed a red glare of some sort in the sky as i was walking towards my street. the red light disappeared. as i'm getting near my house i noticed something moving towards my direction in the sky. i stopped to watch it and it was coming towards me. as it got closer i could see it was a circular disc shaped object completely silent flying. it had a small circular glow, not too bright in the center and i could tell it was bigger than the glow. it flew above my head and then turned fast and smoothly in another direction. it traveled fast towards me but slowed down as it got closer before it turned. as it headed in its new direction i could see the top of it. it looked like the typical flying saucer and i thought about chasing it on foot but that wouldbe been impossible and it disappeared as it kept going. the object looked less than 500 ft above me. it was night time so i could barely make notice of its details. but the little bit of light that caught it looked kinda shiny. thats duration was maybe 3-5 minutes in its entirety from start to finish.It happened after midnight after the 4th of july.
content.summary: Flew towards my direction. flew over me, kept flying

content.detailedDescription: 3 of my friends and i were walking down my street with my dog. i'm assuming it was almost 2 am on july 1st; there was a cloudless sky. we were all spread out on the street, i was facing west, 2 of my friends both looking south and one facing west. the one facing west experienced a bright light that he thought was a car which caused him to turn around. the two facing south had the best view of the ufo and i'll try my best to describe what i did not see based off of them. i'm someone who is constantly star gazing night sky, but at this moment i was facing the opposite direction of the ufo and looking 'down' at my dog. i few moments before this occurred i was thinking about an encounter story i had watched on tv; a group of friends had been paralyzed by a extremely bright blue light. i have no explanation why i did this; i saw no light behind me nor hear anything. my friends were all silent as i rolled my head back towards to se. i didn't even look at my friends just directly to the object. it was a large circular orb that was heading towards ew i believe. the tail of it was extremely vivid and long. it was mainly white/blue but there were yellowish sparks coming of the tail. i was the only one that heard a very slight swooshing/humming sound yet i was farthest from it. my boyfriend saw the most of it and he said it moved slowly across the sky then shot off. he wasn't going to say anything because he didn't think anyone else saw it. at i first thought it was a firework but it was way to large to be a firework. my dog didn't even flinch when it occurred. we had so many conversations about space and aliens leading up to this effect and thats what really freaked me out. it was defiantly something i'll never forget.
content.summary: Looked like a large firework, had an extremely vivid tail, 4 witnesses.

content.detailedDescription: So i went out in my front yard at 9:00pm and took up my normal viewing position facing wnw sky with my head swiveling to the n and then to the e back and forth like i usually do at this time of night. 9:10pm and i'm still scanning the sky w, nw, n, e and see nothing but the fog rolling in from the west. 9:13pm and i'm getting bored and for whatever reason i decide to turn around and look to the south, which i never normally do, and at a distance of 1/2 mile to 1 mile and 30 degrees of the horizon i see a light red plasma oval about 100 feet long slowly flying and ascending from sw to ne. the plasma coming off the object was obviously being affected by the fact that this object was in motion. the plasma was being whipped up around this object as it flew. it then made a gentle turn to the sw then steadily climbed at a 60 degree angle until it became star-like a few seconds later. i video'd it (140mb) with my cell phone and tried to upload it but the mufon page timed out. the video looked nothing like what i saw with my eyes, either in color or size of the object, so you ain't missing a thing really, other than me talking to myself as i was filming it. the object was dead silent as it flew. i need to get a better camera or a flir attachment for my phone cause the video simply looks like crap, even on a samsung note 4.
content.summary: 9:13pm, 3 miles nw of lax, light red plasma oval slowly ascending and headed ne, then made a gentle se turn and steadily climbed at a 60 degree angle.

content.detailedDescription: At work 2300-0700 hrs night security ottawa ontario. time of event midnight. sitting at picnic table having cigarette/coffee break looking up south, west, and above head at stars in the clear sky. movement- noticed star like objects moving same speed coming towards my direction(east)or so it appeared. thought was star or manmade satellite until realized i've seen this object before on 2 other occasions and few others employees on location have also stated they witnessed similar objects in sky in past; which left them speechless. objects looked like stars or manmade satellites but moved same speed never got any further away or closer to each other they seemed to maintain certain distance from each other(as if well at least i believe resemble front and back lights of manmade vehicles) as obvious as is it might sound. followed for 20-30 seconds with eyes not taking eyes off until vanished behind building out of view(even when lead hand approached to say hi). lead hand from assembly line(which i believe to be very trustworthy credible individual) was witness to event as she was on her lunch break and walked out to smoking area to have a cigarette approximately 10 seconds after i initially started tracking the ufo's/unknown objects. i stated" am i going crazy seeing things or are those two stars moving at same speed?" she said yeeeeeeeees they appear to be we both kept eyes on objects for few more seconds then disappeared out of view behind building. nothing really surprises me anymore wild and crazy world we live on/in with lots of unknowns, mysteries and questions that need and hopefully will be answered in time. my belief is that this object/s or ufo may be of human origin particularly military as the object does not seem to care about the quickness in which it travels. thank you for your time. have a great day and good luck to all those out there searching for the truth!!!
content.summary: 2 star like objects travelling at what seemed to be same speed/velocity heading from west to east in direction sluggish rate of speed brightness of star like objects changed

content.detailedDescription: Me and my neighbor, marvin jackson, since deceased, we're sitting in his front yard talking, which we often did. i noticed a large bright light about 20 degrees above the horizon.I brought it to marvin's attention,and he said it was an airplane.I thought it could be an airplane also.The airport is to our south about 4 miles. as it got closer i noticed it wasn't going to land at the airport. the object flew directly overhead in between mine and marvin's house it didn't make a sound and it was only 20 to 30 feet above the trees. the lights were on the bottom of the craft shining straight down and very bright. the lights and the surrounding  trees kept me from seeing the object clear enough to make out the exact shape. the object was flying very slow maybe 25 to 30 mph. it continued on a northwest path till it was out of sight. i didn't have a camera nearby because i've never seen a ufo and never believed i would. i was sort of frightened by the sighting because for me it just confirmed that ufo's do exist. i don't know for sure what it was but i've seen reports on television of people seeing something similar.
content.summary: Could not make out color or shape due to brightness of lights6

content.detailedDescription: at the time of the sighing, i was walking my dogs outside. i noticed a fireball like orb in the sky, which i had seen before so it grabbed my attention as another ufo type object. i stopped to watch it and right when i was about to pull up my camera to film it flashed brightly before slowly turning into a barely visible object.   i kept my eye on it because i could still see it and i didn't want to lose it. i wanted to see if it would turn back into the bright orb again. so i watched it as it moved east through hollywood towards downtown los angeles before descending quickly towards earth. as it flew downwards it seem to morph into a very large black almost sheet like parachute object and then it disappeared and i couldn't see where it landed. one of the most fascinating thing i've ever seen!  amazing.
content.summary: Bright orb that turned to a barely visible moving object then quickly descended while expanding into a dark, parachute like formation.

content.detailedDescription:
Went out to count satellites (and beat the heat in my trailer). a sudden flash of light caught my eye about where the handle of the big dipper       joins the "bowl". got to watching that area, and randomly a light would fade in and then out, and then suddenly there would be a bright white flash. it was moving so slowly across the sky that it was difficult to see that it was moving at all. but in watching this phenomenon for a good five minutes, it slowly traveled the length of the big dipper's handle.

i jumped up and ran inside to get my binoculars, which took all of twenty seconds. when i got back outside, the "object" had completely vanished. kept watching, but only saw a few satellites and shooting stars after that.

i've investigated over 2000 ufo reports myself, and frequently observe the night sky. i've never seen or heard of anything like this before.
content.summary: Randomly flashing light just below the handle of the big dipper.

content.detailedDescription: We were on the front porch watching the night sky and fireworks. we saw this object twice. the objects took the same path; about three minutes apart, approximately. the object was moving across the sky from a west direction to an east direction. it didn't move like a plane. we had been seeing planes that evening, but this didn't make any sounds, nor were there any trails behind it. it just appeared in front of us. we didn't know what the object was, because it didn't look like anything we had seen during the evening or ever. the object made a straight path. it didn't waiver or move erratically. it was this yellow-orange ball of light that flew silently. we felt astounded and confused over this sighting. the object made a sudden appearance and when it was going east, it just disappeared.
content.summary: Brilliant yellow-orange flying flame-like object

i don't know if it is a bird, bug, or ?????.  i just don't know.

content.detailedDescription: I was on my break at work, and was looking at the clouds before the storm i took a picture and then is the background there appeared to be 4 balls of light just sitting there i took my phone down and nothing was there i captured the photo on my cell phone

content.detailedDescription: My husband and i were outdoors in our lounge chairs looking at the stars. it was ten minutes after midnight when these bright glowing orbs came out of the south heading north. there were four orbs lined up following each other in a straight line and spaced evenly apart. they were brilliant solid yellow in the center with a red translucent glow surrounding the center. all were the same size and looked identical. we live in an area with a lot of trees. the orbs where low but above our tall oak trees and disappeared going north beyond the trees. suddenly a fifth orb came out of the south following the same path and looked identical to the other four. there was no sound. we looked for a structure that the lights might be attached to but they appeared to be independent of each other. it is hard to determine the speed. we watched them for about 45 seconds. i am the same person who reported the two solid orange orbs in november 2015. in both cases the lights were brilliant in color and moved almost the same path/direction, height and speed. the orange orbs were smaller in size than the yellow/red orbs.
content.summary: Five bright solid yellow orbs with red translucent glow surrounding the yellow center.

content.detailedDescription: At 9:45 pm on july 3, 2016 my son and i observed an object hovering just east of our home. the object changed colors blinking frequently from red, green, blue, purple and white. suddenly it moved east traveling out of site over the horizon. we captured almost 2 minutes of cell phone video. i also enlarged screenshots of the video, where a more defined shape can be seen.
content.summary: When observed object hovering with blinking lights that changed colors. enlarged screenshots show rectangle shaped object with beam lights.

content.detailedDescription:
1) at home, looking out window
2) very bright, first thing i noticed in the sky
3) i thought it was a helicopter as it appeared stationary (therefore, a helicopter coming towards), but it was very very high up.
4) bright orange orb. it was mostly stationary, but then started moving in short square movements, fizzled out, and then appeared 3-4 seconds later for a few more seconds and then become very faint (but still same size). then it fizzled out again.
5) bewildered. intrigued
6) it fizzled out, reappeared (very faint but still same size), then fizzled out again.
content.summary: Bright orange orb, short square movements

content.detailedDescription: I had recently watched the film "sirius" and had begun to engage in intense meditations at night with the intention of initiating contact with extraterrestrial life. i was on my back porch meditating on the night in question. my concentration was broken however when i heard a rush of wind approaching in the distance. it made no mechanical noise, whatsoever, throughout the entire event. i tried to ignore the sound until it grew so loud it sounded as if it were right above me. my view being obstructed by the awning over the porch, i stepped down the stairs and into the grass. as i looked around, a craft slowly appeared from behind. it was incredibly large with no visible wings, or any other appendages. it was a simple cigar shape, but at least the length of a football field. it was perfectly camouflaged to blend in with the night sky. i was only able to see it due to the slight shift in depth perception around the craft, since it was only traveling at a height just above the treetops. as it appeared from the south, i observed 3 white lights on the craft in the shape of a large isosceles triangle. once the original triangle was centered above me, a second set of 3 red lights appeared within the white triangle to form its own smaller isosceles triangle. it continued north in a straight line until out of sight. i attempted to follow in my car but quickly lost sight of the craft.
content.summary: Large camouflaged ufo approached south-to-north silently with triangular light formations

content.detailedDescription: I was sitting on my deck at about 6:00 in the evening when i looked up and saw a silver object in the sky. i live on a flight path for planes landing at the airport so i figured it was a plane. it didn't appear to be moving so i thought it was just coming straight toward me. a white light flashed on the left side and then right in the center of the object a very very bright white light came on and grew until you couldn't see the object anymore and then went off. when it turned off the object was gone and there was nowhere it could go without being seen. the sky was crystal clear and there were no clouds. it just disappeared. has anyone ever reported anything like this before? i'm really curious what it may have been and can't stop thinking about it. if you may have any idea i would like to here from you.
content.summary: Saw object, bright light flashed, object was gone

content.detailedDescription:
This image was taken with my iphone 6. i took this picture because i thought it was cool that the jet looked like a rocket taking off into outer space. 
1. i was in the alley way behind my house. taking out the trash. 
2. i did not notice the "other" objects at the time i took the picture. 
3. i thought it was a commercial jet, because the reason for my picture was that the jet looked like it was a rocket taking off into outer space :)
4. n/a as i did not notice the other objects until well after the image was taken. 
5. n/a see no. 4
6. n/a see no. 4

as i said. the jet looked like it was a rocket so i took 2 images. one normal, and one zoomed in. i took the picture knowing full well that the jet was only heading towards me but looked like a rocket going into space. last night i was reviewing some images on my phone and noticed a couple other things that "freaked" me out. 
1. the portion of a circle, middle to bottom right of the sky in the image. 
friends seem to think it's planet x 
2. top right corner of the sky. looks like the space station but clearly it can't be. it's way too big for it to be the international space station. however as you can see it has lights and what looks like legs, or solar wings like the space station. 
i just want someone to do what they do best and explain what the heck these 2 things are. it doesn't make sense to me. 
first image is the first "normal" picture i took 
second image is my close up of the jet (as that was my focus)
third image is me using "snappen" to point out the obvious objects in question. 
ps there is no possible way i manged to get part of planet x and the unexplained object in one picture. that's just too convenient. i just want an explanation please and thanks.
content.summary: Unknown
